506
00:27:49,080 --> 00:27:50,760
We need to target his weaknesses.

507
00:27:51,240 --> 00:27:53,200
Sadly, very few come to mind.

508
00:27:54,480 --> 00:27:55,880
I can think of one.

509
00:27:56,680 --> 00:27:57,840
Me.

510
00:27:58,640 --> 00:28:01,000
He wants me and he always has.

511
00:28:01,080 --> 00:28:03,520
So if I can get close enough
to him, then...

512
00:28:03,600 --> 00:28:05,240
Then he'll kill you.

513
00:28:05,320 --> 00:28:07,840
Thank you for the vote of confidence,

514
00:28:07,920 --> 00:28:09,560
but I don't need your protection.

515
00:28:09,640 --> 00:28:11,160
There's no reason to go alone.

516
00:28:11,720 --> 00:28:13,480
We're part of a team for a reason.

517
00:28:13,560 --> 00:28:17,160
Yes, and the team seems comfortable
with me doing this

518
00:28:17,240 --> 00:28:19,280
so that makes it about you and me.

519
00:28:25,840 --> 00:28:28,040
- Any updates?
- We're making progress.

520
00:28:28,120 --> 00:28:30,320
In the meantime, we need
to get ready to back Kendra up.

521
00:28:30,400 --> 00:28:33,200
She's going into the asylum
to meet Savage tonight.

522
00:28:33,280 --> 00:28:35,760
Another opportunity for you
to see Nurse Carlisle.

523
00:28:37,000 --> 00:28:39,800
Yeah, and apologize.

524
00:28:41,320 --> 00:28:43,040
I warned you, Ms. Lance.

525
00:28:43,120 --> 00:28:47,000
Rushing a repressed woman
from the 1950s into the freewheeling

526
00:28:47,080 --> 00:28:49,400
sexual mores of the 21st century.

527
00:28:49,480 --> 00:28:51,280
Actually, I was the one
who freaked out.

528
00:28:53,400 --> 00:28:57,280
Ever since I got brought
back to life, I haven't really

529
00:28:58,440 --> 00:29:01,040
experienced much
in the way of feelings.

530
00:29:01,120 --> 00:29:04,200
And then when Lindsey kissed me.

531
00:29:04,280 --> 00:29:07,320
It was like you were being kissed
for the first time.

532
00:29:08,720 --> 00:29:11,480
- How romantic.
- It was more like terrifying.

533
00:29:12,680 --> 00:29:15,320
That's the thing
that sucks about feelings is,

534
00:29:15,400 --> 00:29:18,240
you realize how much
you can hurt someone

535
00:29:19,400 --> 00:29:21,800
or get hurt.

536
00:29:23,880 --> 00:29:25,360
Wakey, wakey.

537
00:29:28,680 --> 00:29:31,480
Do the words "police brutality"
mean anything to you?

538
00:29:31,560 --> 00:29:32,880
You think this is brutal?

539
00:29:32,960 --> 00:29:36,400
You'll be begging for me
after he gets through with you.

540
00:29:36,480 --> 00:29:40,000
That's enough, Sheriff.
Thank you. Leave us be.

541
00:29:41,080 --> 00:29:44,360
This young man and I have a lot
to discuss.

542
00:29:44,440 --> 00:29:47,240
Forgive my friend for his ignorance.

543
00:29:47,320 --> 00:29:50,320
You will learn
that I'm much more enlightened.

544
00:29:50,400 --> 00:29:52,680
Well, I'll take racist
over crazy any day.

545
00:29:52,760 --> 00:29:57,520
Oh, I would hardly describe
what I'm doing here as... as "crazy."

546
00:29:58,160 --> 00:30:02,560
Therapy is nothing more than
a process of self-discovery.

547
00:30:02,640 --> 00:30:06,880
You're about to experience
an extraterrestrial power.

548
00:30:06,960 --> 00:30:08,040
Shall we begin?

549
00:30:34,640 --> 00:30:37,040
What a piece of work is man.

550
00:30:38,680 --> 00:30:40,520
When I was exposed to a meteorite,

551
00:30:40,600 --> 00:30:44,720
I was blessed with eternal life,
immortality.

552
00:30:45,400 --> 00:30:50,200
But sadly, the effect of this
meteorite turned out quite different.

553
00:30:51,800 --> 00:30:53,360
But no less advantageous.

554
00:30:54,600 --> 00:30:56,440
Doc, you have a visitor.

555
00:31:13,080 --> 00:31:14,600
What a pleasant surprise.

556
00:31:15,360 --> 00:31:16,640
Is it a surprise

557
00:31:17,520 --> 00:31:18,520
or fate?

558
00:31:19,840 --> 00:31:22,320
We didn't get to finish
our discussion the other night.

559
00:31:22,400 --> 00:31:25,280
What of your square-jawed
husband, Raymond?

560
00:31:26,240 --> 00:31:28,400
I didn't come here to talk
about my husband,

561
00:31:29,160 --> 00:31:30,160
Doctor.

562
00:31:31,560 --> 00:31:32,560
May I?

563
00:31:34,560 --> 00:31:35,720
May I take your coat?

564
00:31:41,200 --> 00:31:42,760
<i>Make yourself comfortable.</i>

565
00:31:42,840 --> 00:31:43,840
Nurse?

566
00:31:44,280 --> 00:31:46,120
Nurse, I keep hearing
voices in my head.

567
00:31:46,200 --> 00:31:48,840
My wife with another man

568
00:31:49,720 --> 00:31:51,000
and it's driving me crazy.

569
00:31:51,080 --> 00:31:53,960
Well, maybe you should learn
to trust your wife a little bit more.

570
00:31:54,600 --> 00:31:55,600
Orderly?

571
00:31:56,280 --> 00:31:57,880
Show our new patient to his room.

572
00:31:58,920 --> 00:32:02,880
And don't hesitate to give him
a sedative if he doesn't calm down.

573
00:32:02,960 --> 00:32:04,240
Right away, Nurse.

574
00:32:14,960 --> 00:32:16,880
I'm sure the kid is fine.

575
00:32:16,960 --> 00:32:19,480
Jefferson and I, as you know,
share a psychic connection,

576
00:32:19,560 --> 00:32:23,440
but for some inexplicable reason,
I can't seem to reach him.

577
00:32:24,520 --> 00:32:26,600
I've grown so accustomed
to our partnership,

578
00:32:26,680 --> 00:32:28,920
to suddenly be without him
is disquieting.

579
00:32:29,000 --> 00:32:30,640
I know the feeling.

580
00:32:34,600 --> 00:32:37,880
So have you tried
psychoanalysis before?

581
00:32:37,960 --> 00:32:38,960
No.

582
00:32:39,960 --> 00:32:43,720
- My husband thinks it's baloney.
- Oh, is that so?

583
00:32:44,600 --> 00:32:47,920
Well, my specialty is
interpreting dreams.

584
00:32:48,760 --> 00:32:50,320
What do you dream, Kendra?

585
00:32:50,400 --> 00:32:51,720
To be honest,

586
00:32:53,200 --> 00:32:56,400
I've dreamt of you before and me

587
00:32:58,360 --> 00:32:59,360
together.

588
00:33:00,400 --> 00:33:01,800
Well, that's interesting.

589
00:33:02,880 --> 00:33:06,040
And what do we do in those dreams?

590
00:33:07,040 --> 00:33:08,720
I'm afraid you'll think me forward.

591
00:33:08,800 --> 00:33:10,560
Oh, but you are forward.

592
00:33:11,360 --> 00:33:14,360
Coming here in that dress?

593
00:33:14,440 --> 00:33:17,240
Perhaps you should learn
to embrace your desires

594
00:33:17,320 --> 00:33:19,440
so the two of us
can finally be together.

595
00:33:26,880 --> 00:33:28,400
Did you lose something?

596
00:33:30,360 --> 00:33:34,360
I was wondering how long you could
play out this little charade.

597
00:33:34,440 --> 00:33:38,360
You show up on my doorstep
and then my dagger goes missing?

598
00:33:38,440 --> 00:33:43,800
You must think me stupid not to
suspect that your powers had emerged.

599
00:33:48,600 --> 00:33:49,720
Well, well, well.

600
00:33:49,800 --> 00:33:53,080
An FBI agent moonlighting
at the loony bin.

601
00:33:53,160 --> 00:33:55,760
I'm afraid both of you boys
have some explaining to do

602
00:33:55,840 --> 00:33:57,080
down at the station.

603
00:33:57,960 --> 00:34:00,400
Who else have you brought
to the asylum tonight?

604
00:34:00,480 --> 00:34:02,960
No one. No one! It's just me.

605
00:34:03,040 --> 00:34:06,240
I hope you're better at lying
in your next life.

606
00:34:12,160 --> 00:34:13,160
Oh, boy.

607
00:34:13,240 --> 00:34:15,040
Just when you think
you've seen everything.

608
00:34:21,920 --> 00:34:24,400
Guess those missing kids
are no longer missing.

609
00:34:26,000 --> 00:34:27,160
What have you done?

610
00:34:28,000 --> 00:34:30,400
I released my test subjects.

611
00:34:30,480 --> 00:34:33,640
The energy from the meteorite
has changed them.

612
00:34:33,720 --> 00:34:37,560
I set out to build an army
as powerful as you.

613
00:34:37,640 --> 00:34:40,280
Pity they didn't turn out
nearly as beautiful.

614
00:34:52,280 --> 00:34:53,400
Oh, my God.

615
00:34:54,800 --> 00:34:55,880
It's Jefferson.

616
00:34:57,640 --> 00:34:59,440
Jefferson, it's... it's us!

617
00:35:05,360 --> 00:35:07,360
Jax, don't make me do this.

618
00:35:26,560 --> 00:35:27,560
I'll deal with this lot.

619
00:35:27,640 --> 00:35:28,760
Find Kendra now.

620
00:35:54,040 --> 00:35:56,960
I can explain. Just not now.

621
00:36:05,520 --> 00:36:08,880
Perhaps it will turn out better
in our next life, my love.

622
00:36:12,000 --> 00:36:13,080
Are you okay?

623
00:36:29,760 --> 00:36:30,960
It's time to go.

624
00:36:32,400 --> 00:36:34,000
Not without Jefferson.

625
00:36:34,080 --> 00:36:35,720
Or whatever's left of him.

626
00:36:38,680 --> 00:36:42,000
Gideon was able to help me devise
a gene therapy that will hopefully

627
00:36:42,080 --> 00:36:45,160
restore Jefferson and those at
the asylum to their former selves.

628
00:36:45,240 --> 00:36:48,520
If genome bonding occurs,
we should know right away.

629
00:36:48,600 --> 00:36:51,000
Course, we would never have had
the slightest chance of saving him

630
00:36:51,080 --> 00:36:52,080
were it not for you.

631
00:36:52,160 --> 00:36:53,800
Let's not get sentimental.

632
00:36:53,880 --> 00:36:57,320
Another minute and things might have
gone down very differently.

633
00:36:57,400 --> 00:36:59,400
Despite your bravado, Mr. Snart

634
00:37:00,320 --> 00:37:03,960
the actions that I witnessed last
night were nothing short of heroic.

635
00:37:12,560 --> 00:37:13,840
It's working.

636
00:37:21,000 --> 00:37:22,160
Hey.

637
00:37:23,040 --> 00:37:25,000
How are our friends
doing over in Hall H?

638
00:37:25,080 --> 00:37:28,440
Whatever Dr. Stein gave those
creatures seemed to have worked.

639
00:37:28,520 --> 00:37:29,720
They're back to normal.

640
00:37:33,200 --> 00:37:34,200
And you?

641
00:37:35,320 --> 00:37:38,080
Not sure if I'm ever gonna get
fully back to normal.

642
00:37:39,440 --> 00:37:40,440
Good.

643
00:37:50,200 --> 00:37:51,400
Thank you

644
00:37:52,040 --> 00:37:53,320
for rescuing me.

645
00:37:54,000 --> 00:37:57,280
Well, you rescued me first,
so now we're even.

646
00:37:59,440 --> 00:38:00,920
You have to go, don't you?

647
00:38:02,280 --> 00:38:03,280
I get it.

648
00:38:04,360 --> 00:38:07,040
Should've known better
than to fall for a ninja.

649
00:38:11,760 --> 00:38:14,560
Who knows?
Maybe I'll be back one day.

650
00:38:14,640 --> 00:38:15,760
And if so...

651
00:38:16,400 --> 00:38:17,440
You know where to find me.

652
00:38:23,560 --> 00:38:26,480
So, I felt bad about trashing
your dad's.

653
00:38:26,560 --> 00:38:28,160
I thought this might make up for it.

654
00:38:28,760 --> 00:38:31,200
- You bought me a car?
- I souped it up too.

655
00:38:31,280 --> 00:38:33,240
In case of future monster attacks.

656
00:38:35,560 --> 00:38:36,960
I wish you didn't have to go.

657
00:38:38,040 --> 00:38:39,440
I don't belong here.

658
00:38:40,040 --> 00:38:41,160
And neither do you.

659
00:38:41,880 --> 00:38:43,840
Promise me you'll
get out of this town.

660
00:38:43,920 --> 00:38:44,960
The both of you.

661
00:38:46,080 --> 00:38:47,160
Tommy!

662
00:38:47,920 --> 00:38:49,680
It's a great big world out there,
Betty.

663
00:38:49,760 --> 00:38:51,120
And it's changing fast.

664
00:38:51,960 --> 00:38:53,920
Maybe we'll catch up down
the road somewhere.

665
00:39:01,560 --> 00:39:03,720
Hey. I was just packing up.

666
00:39:03,800 --> 00:39:05,160
I thought you were back
at the Waverider.

667
00:39:05,240 --> 00:39:06,480
I just forgot something.

668
00:39:07,440 --> 00:39:08,840
I forgot to say I'm sorry.

669
00:39:09,800 --> 00:39:10,840
Look, I was wrong to think

670
00:39:10,920 --> 00:39:14,360
that I could actually end
Savage by myself.

671
00:39:14,440 --> 00:39:15,680
Just slow down.

672
00:39:16,600 --> 00:39:17,680
I made a mistake too.

673
00:39:18,320 --> 00:39:20,120
I got so caught up playing house

674
00:39:20,200 --> 00:39:23,200
that I forgot about why
we were really here.

675
00:39:24,000 --> 00:39:25,960
And you will end Savage someday.

676
00:39:27,160 --> 00:39:29,840
I guess the last thing
a 4,000-year-old demigoddess needs

677
00:39:29,920 --> 00:39:31,720
is an overprotective husband.

678
00:39:32,880 --> 00:39:35,480
What she needs is a partner.

679
00:39:36,680 --> 00:39:37,680
What do you say?

680
00:39:42,240 --> 00:39:43,240
Partner.

681
00:39:54,160 --> 00:39:56,080
Well, look who's up and around.

682
00:39:57,280 --> 00:39:58,280
Yeah.

683
00:39:59,400 --> 00:40:01,240
I guess I owe you an apology.

684
00:40:01,800 --> 00:40:04,560
Grey told me about what happened
back at the asylum.

685
00:40:05,080 --> 00:40:07,400
You had the chance to kill me
and you didn't.

686
00:40:08,320 --> 00:40:10,640
After last night, I know enough
about being a monster

687
00:40:10,720 --> 00:40:11,720
to know that you're not one.

688
00:40:11,800 --> 00:40:14,120
Stop. I'm getting misty eyed.

689
00:40:15,440 --> 00:40:16,640
I just want you to know

690
00:40:17,840 --> 00:40:19,400
about what happened with Rory?

691
00:40:20,200 --> 00:40:21,200
I get it.

692
00:40:22,160 --> 00:40:23,720
You were protecting us.

693
00:40:23,800 --> 00:40:24,840
And that doesn't make you a murderer.

694
00:40:24,920 --> 00:40:26,760
It makes you a part of this team.

695
00:40:26,840 --> 00:40:28,560
Jefferson, you should be resting.

696
00:40:28,640 --> 00:40:30,440
Man, I'm... I'm done laying around.

697
00:40:30,520 --> 00:40:32,080
I just want to get
the hell out of Mayberry.

698
00:40:32,160 --> 00:40:36,360
Agreed, we're still waiting on Sara
and the two lovebirds to get back.

699
00:40:36,440 --> 00:40:40,200
Seems they've taken quite
a shine to 1958.

700
00:40:41,600 --> 00:40:43,760
- What on earth?
- Gideon?

701
00:40:45,440 --> 00:40:46,640
Not this guy again.

702
00:40:46,720 --> 00:40:48,920
<i>Captain, Chronos has breached
the starboard hatch.</i>

703
00:40:49,000 --> 00:40:50,000
How is that possible?

704
00:40:50,080 --> 00:40:51,080
Clearly, he's received some new toys

705
00:40:51,160 --> 00:40:53,080
from his Time Master friends
since our last encounter.

706
00:40:53,160 --> 00:40:55,960
Gideon, seal the bulkheads
from here until...

707
00:41:03,720 --> 00:41:04,760
Grey, come on. Let us do this.

708
00:41:04,840 --> 00:41:07,840
If we merge on the Waverider,
we could destroy the entire ship!

709
00:41:07,920 --> 00:41:10,440
Are you not paying attention
to what Chronos is doing?

710
00:41:11,360 --> 00:41:12,680
Fall back!

711
00:41:12,760 --> 00:41:14,280
Get to the jump ship!

712
00:41:19,120 --> 00:41:22,640
1958's swell and all
but I miss the Internet

713
00:41:23,200 --> 00:41:24,720
and cell phones.

714
00:41:30,360 --> 00:41:31,440
What are they doing?

715
00:41:32,120 --> 00:41:33,240
- Hey.
- Hey!

716
00:41:37,800 --> 00:41:39,200
Where did they go?

717
00:41:40,520 --> 00:41:43,960
Better question,
why did they leave us?

